:<!--Trigger PerformanceE 504087001: Config/Level/Mission/5040870/Act/Act504087001.json-->
:'''Zeno:''' Dear Parmenides, I won't plague you with strange questions anymore &mdash; just one: Why don't you flee?
:'''Parmenides:''' Ha, Zeno, my old friend! Since you show concern, I'll answer: I believe souls endure, finding new vessels in the Era Nova. Why don't you flee?
:'''Zeno:''' Contrary to you, I think souls depend on flesh – death scatters both. Fleeing's meaningless.
:'''Parmenides:''' Oh, wise listener – why don't you flee?
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} I fear nothing.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504087008-->
::'''Parmenides:''' Then let us hear the final debate between these two rhetoric teachers. Such gravely mistaken views mustn't be allowed to poison the afterlife.
::'''Parmenides:''' I must declare that the soul is but a form, and the body is merely its material vessel. If souls don't exist, what converses with me now? Where do your senses dwell, your thoughts reside, your actions originate?
::'''Zeno:''' The answer lies precisely within the flesh, Parmenides! My ears hear your voice, my eyes behold your form. When you spout nonsense, blood burns my cheeks with secondhand shame.
::'''Parmenides:''' Yet priests and the Chrysos Heirs often claim to see souls. How would you explain this?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Yeah...
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} This worldview does allow us to see souls.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I've seen them too.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504087015-->
::'''Zeno:''' Those unfeeling, unresponsive reflections of the past differ not from your own reflection in the mirror.
::'''Zeno:''' Indivisible particles compose our world and bodies. Their movements, order and combinations follow patterns, not infinite possibilities.
::'''Zeno:''' Thoughts, desires, actions &mdash; what we call "soul" is but predetermined permutations of possibilities.
::'''Parmenides:''' How pitiful if you're fated to entertain such absurd notions! If souls don't exist, who dictates these possibilities? Who chooses our fates?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The gods?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Ourselves?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Or just by random chance?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504087022-->
::'''Parmenides:''' No &mdash; the soul! As a form, it's the cause and purpose of our existence and actions. It defines our being, actualizing the body's latent potential to become ourselves.
::'''Zeno:''' Preposterous! Look around &mdash; the world shatters, time derails. Yet here we await death through sophistry. Your soul must be pickled in honey brew to seek such actualization!
::'''Parmenides:''' Yours is pickled! The natural form isn't like soap, it will not produce colorful bubbles. Add more salt to harden your reasoning.
::'''Zeno:''' You dare lecture me? My trimmed nails caused hair loss during last haircut. Provoke me, and I'll show you the wrath of a dromas!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} ...What are you guys talking about?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} No fighting, please.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Kind words form friendly bonds, and harsh ones break the heart.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504087029-->
::'''Zeno:''' Ah, what's happening? Why are we talking... such nonsense?
::'''Parmenides:''' Likely due to {{Rubi|Cerces|Reason Titan}}' fall, reason and logic has grown unstable.
::'''Zeno:''' Then why debate? At this point, we have nowhere left to go.
::'''Parmenides:''' Indeed, nowhere.
::'''Zeno:''' Only this remains certain.
:{{DIcon|Arrow}} Where can I run to?
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504087008-->
